-- UK house prices fall for first time in 16 months - Nationwide
-- By David Milliken
-- Tue Sep 30, 2014 02:22AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 30 (Reuters) - British mortgage lender Nationwide recorded the first monthly fall in house prices for more than a year this month, causing the annual rate of house price growth to fall to an eight-month low.

Nationwide said that average house prices across Britain fell by 0.2 percent in September - the first drop in 16 months - after rising by 0.8 percent in August.